==English==
===Noun===
'''oxgang'''
#{{archaic}} the [[area]] of [[land]] that could be [[ploughed]] by an [[ox]] in a [[day]]; one eighth of a [[carucate]]
===Synonyms===
*[[bovate]]
===Usage notes===
* Since land was normally ploughed with a team of eight oxen, it is actually an eighth share of the land ploughed by an ox team in a day.